SIMPLE: professional
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Professional
<hw>Pro*fes"sion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to a profession, or calling; conforming to the rules or
standards of a profession; following a profession; <as>as,
<ex>professional</ex> knowledge; <ex>professional</ex>
conduct.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧Pride, not personal, but
<xex>professional</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Macaulay.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>professional</xex> sneerer.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>De Quincey.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Engaged in by professionals; <as>as, a
<ex>professional</ex> race</as>; -- opposed to
<contr>amateur</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Professional</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Professional
<hw>Pro*fes"sion*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person who prosecutes
anything professionally, or for a livelihood, and not in the character
of an amateur; a professional worker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Professionalism</ent>⟦br⟧
